Welcome to **powerglide** ⚡ — the CLI coding agent that slides.

> **Why powerglide?** Built in [Zig 0.15.2](https://ziglang.org/), powerglide orchestrates swarms of SWE (Software Engineering) agents with precise velocity control, reliable PTY management, and multi-model routing. Everything ships as a single fast binary with zero runtime dependencies.

Named after the legendary Lamborghini Powerglide transmission, powerglide is built for one purpose: **maximum throughput**.

```bash
$ powerglide run --agent hephaestus --velocity 2.0 "implement a binary search tree in Zig"
```

## Key Features

- **Multi-Agent Swarms** 🐜 — Run N agents in parallel with independent workspaces, task queues, and health monitoring. Rogue agents get auto-terminated via heartbeat timeouts and step limits.

- **Velocity Control** 🚀 — Tune agent speed on the fly: `--velocity 2.0` (fast) or `0.5` (conservative). Agents self-tune through session config files.

- **Ralph Loop State Machine** 🔄 — Fault-tolerant `idle → thinking → acting → observing → commit` cycle with explicit `POWERGLIDE_DONE` stop signals and configurable max steps.

- **Reliable PTY Management** 💻 — Full pseudoterminal support using `waitpid` for exit-code capture, WNOHANG polling, and `/proc/<pid>/status` fallback.

- **Multi-Model Routing** 🤖 — Route to Anthropic (Claude), OpenAI-compatible APIs (Ollama, NVIDIA NIM, Together AI), or any local provider. Automatic fallback chains included.

- **Terminal TUI** 📊 — Multi-panel vxfw dashboard showing agent status, log streaming, and live velocity display.

## Quick Start

### Get Started

- [Zig 0.15.2](https://ziglang.org/download/) — Install with `mise install zig@0.15.2` or from the official site
- An API key for your model provider (set `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` or `OPENAI_API_KEY`)

### Build

```bash
git clone https://github.com/bkataru/powerglide
cd powerglide
zig build
```

The binary lands at `./zig-out/bin/powerglide`.

### Run

```bash
# Health check — verify all dependencies are set up
./zig-out/bin/powerglide doctor

# Run an agent session
./zig-out/bin/powerglide run "refactor this function to be more idiomatic"

# Run with specific agent and velocity
./zig-out/bin/powerglide run --agent hephaestus --velocity 2.0 "add unit tests"

# Open TUI dashboard
./zig-out/bin/powerglide tui
```

## Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `powerglide run` | Launch an agent coding session |
| `powerglide session` | Manage agent sessions — list, show, resume, delete, export |
| `powerglide agent` | Manage agent configurations — list, add, remove, show |
| `powerglide swarm` | Manage agent swarms — list, create, add, remove, run, status, stop |
| `powerglide config` | Manage powerglide configuration — show, set, get, reset, edit |
| `powerglide tools` | List and test available tools — list, show, test |
| `powerglide tui` | Open the interactive multi-agent dashboard |
| `powerglide doctor` | Run system health checks |
| `powerglide version` | Show version information |


## The Ralph Loop

powerglide centers on the **Ralph Loop** — a state machine inspired by [ralph](https://github.com/snarktank/ralph) that powers every agent session:

```=html
<svg viewBox="0 0 520 620" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <defs>
    <linearGradient id="rl-amber" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="100%">
      <stop offset="0%" style="stop-color:#F7A41D"/>
      <stop offset="100%" style="stop-color:#d97706"/>
    </linearGradient>
    <linearGradient id="rl-cyan" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="100%">
      <stop offset="0%" style="stop-color:#06b6d4"/>
      <stop offset="100%" style="stop-color:#0891b2"/>
    </linearGradient>
    <linearGradient id="rl-purple" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="100%">
      <stop offset="0%" style="stop-color:#7c3aed"/>
      <stop offset="100%" style="stop-color:#6d28d9"/>
    </linearGradient>
    <filter id="rl-glow" x="-40%" y="-40%" width="180%" height="180%">
      <feGaussianBlur in="SourceGraphic" stdDeviation="3" result="blur"/>
      <feMerge><feMergeNode in="blur"/><feMergeNode in="SourceGraphic"/></feMerge>
    </filter>
    <marker id="rl-arrow" markerWidth="10" markerHeight="7" refX="9" refY="3.5" orient="auto">
      <polygon points="0 0,10 3.5,0 7" fill="#F7A41D"/>
    </marker>
    <marker id="rl-arrow-purple" markerWidth="10" markerHeight="7" refX="9" refY="3.5" orient="auto">
      <polygon points="0 0,10 3.5,0 7" fill="#7c3aed"/>
    </marker>
    <marker id="rl-arrow-pink" markerWidth="10" markerHeight="7" refX="9" refY="3.5" orient="auto">
      <polygon points="0 0,10 3.5,0 7" fill="#ec4899"/>
    </marker>
  </defs>

  <!-- Background -->
  <rect width="520" height="620" fill="#050505" rx="8"/>

  <!-- Grid -->
  <g stroke="#1a1a25" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.4">
    <line x1="130" y1="0" x2="130" y2="620"/>
    <line x1="260" y1="0" x2="260" y2="620"/>
    <line x1="390" y1="0" x2="390" y2="620"/>
    <line x1="0" y1="100" x2="520" y2="100"/>
    <line x1="0" y1="200" x2="520" y2="200"/>
    <line x1="0" y1="300" x2="520" y2="300"/>
    <line x1="0" y1="400" x2="520" y2="400"/>
    <line x1="0" y1="500" x2="520" y2="500"/>
  </g>

  <!-- IDLE (top) -->
  <rect x="175" y="20" width="150" height="38" fill="none" stroke="url(#rl-amber)" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#rl-glow)"/>
  <text x="250" y="44" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="14" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">IDLE</text>

  <!-- Arrow IDLE -> LOAD_TASKS -->
  <line x1="250" y1="58" x2="250" y2="78" stroke="#F7A41D" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#rl-arrow)"/>

  <!-- LOAD_TASKS -->
  <rect x="155" y="82" width="190" height="38" fill="none" stroke="url(#rl-cyan)" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#rl-glow)"/>
  <text x="250" y="106" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">LOAD_TASKS</text>

  <!-- Arrow LOAD_TASKS -> PICK_TASK -->
  <line x1="250" y1="120" x2="250" y2="140" stroke="#F7A41D" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#rl-arrow)"/>

  <!-- PICK_TASK -->
  <rect x="145" y="144" width="210" height="38" fill="none" stroke="url(#rl-cyan)" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#rl-glow)"/>
  <text x="250" y="168" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">PICK_TASK</text>

  <!-- Arrow PICK_TASK -> THINKING -->
  <line x1="250" y1="182" x2="250" y2="202" stroke="#F7A41D" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#rl-arrow)"/>

  <!-- THINKING -->
  <rect x="155" y="206" width="190" height="38" fill="none" stroke="url(#rl-cyan)" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#rl-glow)"/>
  <text x="250" y="230" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">THINKING</text>

  <!-- Arrow THINKING -> TOOL_CALL -->
  <line x1="250" y1="244" x2="250" y2="264" stroke="#F7A41D" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#rl-arrow)"/>

  <!-- TOOL_CALL -->
  <rect x="155" y="268" width="190" height="38" fill="none" stroke="url(#rl-cyan)" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#rl-glow)"/>
  <text x="250" y="292" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">TOOL_CALL</text>

  <!-- Arrow TOOL_CALL -> EXECUTING -->
  <line x1="250" y1="306" x2="250" y2="326" stroke="#F7A41D" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#rl-arrow)"/>

  <!-- EXECUTING -->
  <rect x="155" y="330" width="190" height="38" fill="none" stroke="url(#rl-cyan)" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#rl-glow)"/>
  <text x="250" y="354" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">EXECUTING</text>

  <!-- Arrow EXECUTING -> OBSERVING -->
  <line x1="250" y1="368" x2="250" y2="388" stroke="#F7A41D" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#rl-arrow)"/>

  <!-- OBSERVING -->
  <rect x="155" y="392" width="190" height="38" fill="none" stroke="url(#rl-cyan)" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#rl-glow)"/>
  <text x="250" y="416" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">OBSERVING</text>

  <!-- Arrow OBSERVING -> VERIFY -->
  <line x1="250" y1="430" x2="250" y2="450" stroke="#F7A41D" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#rl-arrow)"/>

  <!-- VERIFY -->
  <rect x="165" y="454" width="170" height="38" fill="none" stroke="url(#rl-purple)" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#rl-glow)"/>
  <text x="250" y="478" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">VERIFY</text>

  <!-- Arrow VERIFY -> COMMIT -->
  <line x1="250" y1="492" x2="250" y2="512" stroke="#F7A41D" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#rl-arrow)"/>

  <!-- COMMIT -->
  <rect x="165" y="516" width="170" height="38" fill="none" stroke="url(#rl-purple)" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#rl-glow)"/>
  <text x="250" y="540" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">COMMIT</text>

  <!-- DONE (bottom right, from LOAD_TASKS "all done?" exit) -->
  <rect x="370" y="82" width="110" height="38" fill="none" stroke="url(#rl-amber)" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#rl-glow)"/>
  <text x="425" y="106" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">DONE</text>

  <!-- Arrow LOAD_TASKS -> DONE (all done?) -->
  <line x1="345" y1="101" x2="365" y2="101" stroke="#06b6d4" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#rl-arrow)"/>
  <text x="355" y="96" text-anchor="middle" fill="#71717a" font-size="9" font-family="monospace">all done</text>

  <!-- Loop back: COMMIT -> LOAD_TASKS -->
  <path d="M 165 535 Q 60 535 60 101 Q 60 82 150 82" fill="none" stroke="#7c3aed" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="6,4" marker-end="url(#rl-arrow-purple)"/>
  <text x="52" y="320" text-anchor="middle" fill="#7c3aed" font-size="9" font-family="monospace" transform="rotate(-90,52,320)">next task</text>

  <!-- FAILED (right side, reachable from any state) -->
  <rect x="370" y="268" width="110" height="38" fill="none" stroke="#ec4899" stroke-width="2" rx="4" filter="url(#rl-glow)"/>
  <text x="425" y="292" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-weight="bold" font-family="monospace">FAILED</text>
  <text x="425" y="325" text-anchor="middle" fill="#71717a" font-size="9" font-family="monospace">on error</text>

  <!-- Arrow from THINKING area to FAILED (error path) -->
  <line x1="345" y1="287" x2="365" y2="287" stroke="#ec4899" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4,3" marker-end="url(#rl-arrow-pink)"/>

  <!-- Corner accents -->
  <g stroke="#7c3aed" stroke-width="2" fill="none" opacity="0.4">
    <path d="M18 18 L28 18 L28 28"/>
    <path d="M502 18 L492 18 L492 28"/>
    <path d="M18 602 L28 602 L28 592"/>
    <path d="M502 602 L492 602 L492 592"/>
  </g>
</svg>
```


The loop emits `<POWERGLIDE_DONE>` when all tasks complete, giving the orchestrator a clean stop signal.

## Inspiration

powerglide draws from the best ideas across the AI coding agent ecosystem:

| Project | What We Borrowed |
|---------|---------------|
| [oh-my-pi](https://github.com/can1357/oh-my-pi) | Multi-agent harness patterns and orchestration |
| [oh-my-opencode](https://github.com/code-yeongyu/oh-my-opencode) | Ralph Wiggum loop and autonomous agent control |
| [ralph](https://github.com/snarktank/ralph) | Ralph loop state machine with explicit done signals |
| [gastown](https://github.com/steveyegge/gastown) | Multi-agent workspace isolation and task queues |
| [opencode](https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode) | CLI UX and multi-model routing |
| [crush](https://github.com/charmbracelet/crush) | Terminal UX and TUI design |


